'''Jinzhou Bay Airport''' ({{zh|s=锦州湾机场}}) {{airport codes|JNZ|ZYJZ}} is an airport serving the city of [[Jinzhou]] in western [[Liaoning]] province of [[Northeast China]]. It is located in Jianye Township, [[Linghai]] city. The airport received approval from the [[State Council of China]] in November 2012. The projected total investment is 762 million [[renminbi|yuan]].<ref name="xinhua">{{cite news |url=http://www.ln.xinhuanet.com/newscenter/2012-11/07/c_113623002.htm |script-title=zh:锦州湾机场通过国家立项审批 |newspaper=Xinhua |language=Chinese |date=2012-11-07 |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

The airport was opened on 10 December 2015, when all flights serving Jinzhou were transferred from the old [[Jinzhou Xiaolingzi Airport]], which became a dedicated military airport.<ref>{{cite news |title=辽宁新增一民用机场架起辽西沟通全国空中桥梁 |url=http://news.carnoc.com/list/331/331030.html |accessdate=2015-12-10 |work=Carnoc |date=2015-12-10}}</ref>

==Facilities==
The airport have a 2,500-meter runway (class 4C) and a 7,200-square-meter terminal building. It is projected to handle 550,000 passengers and 3,750 tons of cargo annually.<ref name="xinhua"/>

